UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Hector L. BACIGALUP, Appellee. No. 6189. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. July 7, 1930.

Before WILBUR, Circuit Judge, and KERRIGAN, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to motion of appellant and stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered, and that mandate issue forthwith.
